{"key":"processedPost-15492126","value":{"id":15492126,"first":15491366,"last":15492927,"when":1323478071,"utime":"12/10/11 02:47 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I have a few clusters at the very bottoms of the cakes the top ones of the clusters are growing up but the ones at the bottoms just grow straight out and end up laying on the perlite.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />That's pretty normal.&nbsp; Slip some wax paper or similar between the fruits and the perlite.<br /><br />Make sure your light is above and to one side, not directly overhead. It's best if it's shining in through the side walls of the terrarium. If directly up, it will reflect off the perlite and fruits low on the cakes will turn downward.<br />RR","title":"Re: fruits growing into perlite?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}